Our Reporter  Singer Khalil who was formerly known as Ghetto P will drop his debut EP titled ‘GROWN’, tomorrow. The EP which has seven tracks will be released on Saturday, January 18 to a live audience in a listening party at FreeMe space, Lekki, Lagos by 8pm.  Tracks in GROWN (The E.P) depicts in different ways love, positivity, hope and fairness. It is partly sensual and some part inspirational.  This project is an epitome of good music and feel good vibes. Khalil show cases his rap prowess while fusing dance hall/hip-hop/pop and icing it all with our beloved afro sound. 